frameDefinitions: An Agent produces a Forgery, an entity that they intend to pass off as a particular (instance of)  a Standard.
A Creator  produces a physical object which is to serve as a Representation of an actual or imagined entity or event, the Represented.
A Creator creates an artifact that is typically an iconic Representation of an actual or imagined entity or event.
This frame describes food and meal preparation.
An Assessor examines a Phenomenon to figure out its Value according to some Feature of the Phenomenon.
A physical object, the Artifact, is produced by a Creator to stimulate the perceptions, emotions, or cognition of an audience.

listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person that creates a Forgery with the intent of passing it off as (an instance of) the <fen>Standard</fen>.
The <fen>Forgery</fen> is the product that the <fen>Agent</fen> creates with the intent of passing it off as (an instance of) the <fen>Standard</fen>.
The <fen>Standard</fen> is the actually existing or imagined (kind of) thing that the <fen>Agent</fen> wants to pass the <fen>Forgery</fen> off as.
The time at which the forgery takes place.
The location in which the <fen>Agent</fen> makes a <fen>Forgery</fen>.
An individual or individuals that bring the <fen>Representation</fen> into existence.
The entity--which may be a thing, an action or a state--that is represented by the <fen>Representation</fen>.
The time at which a <fen>Representation</fen> is created.
The location in which the artist produces the representation.
An individual or individuals that bring the <fen>Representation</fen> into existence.
The entity that is created to represent either iconically or abstractly.
The time at which a <fen>Representation</fen> is created.
The location in which the <fen>Creator</fen> produces the <fen>Representation</fen>.
The <fen>Cook</fen>  prepares the <fen>Produced_food</fen>.
The <fen>Produced_food</fen> is the result of a <fen>Cook</fen>'s efforts.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the cooking creation occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the cooking creation occurs.
The sentient entity that evaluates the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
The entity whose <fen>Value</fen> according to a <fen>Feature</fen> is being measured.
The type of property or feature that the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is being judged on.
An event or procedure that allows the <fen>Assessor</fen> to evaluate the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
<fen>Medium</fen> is the physical entity or channel used by the <fen>Assessor</fen> to make the assessment.
The time at which the <fen>Assessor</fen> makes the assessment.
The location where the assessing takes place.
This role identifies the entity or substance that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Artifact</fen> is presently located.
